data.title: Princess Louisa, Queen of Denmark (1724
data.meta_description: Crown Princess Louisa (1724-51) is shown here wearing the cross of the Union Parfaite. Louisa was the youngest child of George II and Caroline of Brandenburg-Ansbach.  Her mother, Queen Caroline, died in 1737 so, from the age of 13, Louisa was brought up by her elder sister, Princess Caroline Elizabeth.
